summary: This 4.5-Star, Nonstick Pan Is 77 Percent Off Today On Amazon
title: This 4.5-Star, Nonstick Pan Is 77 Percent Off Today On Amazon
body:
From Woman’s Day

View this post on Instagram

Two words: Taco. Tuesday. 🌮 Did you know that properly pre-heating your pan is the key to perfect tacos (or any dish for that matter?) Our Thermo-Spot pattern turns solid red once it reaches ideal temperature. Your stomach will thank you.

A post shared by T-fal (@tfalusa) on Feb 26, 2019 at 1:40pm PST

Pans are the kitchen tool that you can never have too many of…what else is used regularly for breakfast, lunch, and dinner? If you’re in the market for a new one, T-fal’s Nonstick 12-inch Deep Saute Fry Pan is currently marked down a crazy 77 percent on Amazon.

The pan comes with a glass lid and appears to only be sold through Amazon, per T-fal’s website. While its list price is $125, the sale brings it down to just $29, with free shipping on all orders.

It’s popular with Amazon customers; besides being an Amazon’s Choice for nonstick pans, more than 3,000 reviews are available with 79 percent of customers giving it five stars and another 10 percent giving it four stars. It has T-fal’s signature Thermo-Spot Technology that lights up when the pan is perfectly preheated, helping to cook food more evenly and efficiently.

It’s built with an Anti-Warp base that’s also meant to help with heat distribution. While the pan is advertised as dishwasher safe, many customers note in reviews they wash it by hand to better protect the nonstick coating. T-fal says the pan is safe to use with metal, nylon, coated, or wooden utensils.

This isn’t a Deal of the Day, but it is a big mark-down, so we don’t expect it to last too long. Shop soon if you want to take advantage of the sale.

Shop more great kitchenware deals at Slickdeals.com.

blog.name: livinglifewithlucia
blog.title: Living Life with Lucia
blog.description: Hi there and welcome! This blog is all about everything and anything. Life after Uni, perspectives on politics, religion, music and mental health. Then there is my own advice and experiences on life as a teenager going into adulthood - families, relationships, friendships. It all happens to each and everyone of us and this is a place for you to sit, discuss and feel not alone in a world where it can be pretty scary! Some might agree, some might not but I invite you to this page as an online family to read and enjoy my blogs and discuss your own opinions with me! Welcome to Living Life with Lucia!

title: #6 - May, Myself and I - Weight
body:
#6 – May, Myself and I – Weight

Yes, I know, I missed days 4 and 5, but I never promised to get everyday done. I knew it wouldn’t be possible to do it all and so I wasn’t going to set a goal that I already knew I would fail. This is something I have learned to do over the past few years – not setting myself up to fail. It does nothing for my self-confidence and only ends up making me feel grumpy and annoyed at myself for not…

description:
Debating the best job among all 130 college football teams or within any conference is always an ongoing discussion. The debate doesn’t start with a small sample size but should take into account more of a long-term (both past and future) in order to get a better snapshot of the program. Every college football program is unique and has its own set of challenges. But some programs are clearly better than others.

description:
The Chicago Bears have moved onto the next phase of their offseason program as they held their annual rookie minicamp at Halas Hall this past weekend. And aside from the drafted rookies and undrafted free agents, the Bears also brought in numerous players on a tryout basis. Some of those players could get a contract offer heading into the next level of offseason workouts, but many of them will leave without a deal.
